Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Drain the @mozzarella{1%ball} and squeeze out as much liquid as you can. Pat dry with #kitchen paper{}, then tear into small pieces.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{90%g} and sliced pepper and fry until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic, @chipotle paste{20%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and black beans, then fry for ~{1%minute} more.

> Add less chipotle paste if you'd prefer things milder.

Stir the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1%carton} and @sugar{1/2%tsp}(for the sauce) through the bean mixture.

Reduce the heat to medium and simmer until thickened, ~{7-8%minutes}, then mash half the black beans with a #fork{} in the pan. Meanwhile, preheat your #grill{} to high.

Once the sauce has thickened, lay the @plain taco tortillas{6} on a #board{} (3 per person). Reserve a quarter of the bean mixture for the topping, then spoon the remaining bean mixture down the centre of each, then roll them up to enclose the filling.

Drizzle a little @oil{1%drizzle} over the bottom of an #ovenproof dish{}, then lay in the wraps. Pack them snugly, side by side, with the folded edge underneath so they don't unroll.

Top with the reserved bean mixture and torn mozzarella. Grill until golden and the cheese is bubbling, ~{5-6%minutes}.

In a #medium bowl{}, add the @red wine vinegar{12%g}, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%drizzle} and @sugar{1/4%tsp}(for the dressing). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix well.

Just before you're ready to serve, toss the @wild rocket{20%g} in the dressing.

When everything's ready, share your chipotle chorizo enchiladas between your plates.

Serve the salad alongside. Enjoy!